00:07:15.260 --> 00:07:20.760
It's a new set of services that
will be coming to Android

00:07:20.760 --> 00:07:23.220
devices starting from Froyo.

00:07:23.220 --> 00:07:28.600
And it will provide a set of
APIs that will make it easier

00:07:28.600 --> 00:07:33.010
for developers to authorize web
application to get access

00:07:33.010 --> 00:07:36.160
to some Google APIs, such
as Google Drive.

00:07:36.160 --> 00:07:40.165
So, right now, the only way to
get an access token-- well,

00:07:40.165 --> 00:07:42.860
there are two ways.

00:07:42.860 --> 00:07:45.160
The main one is using
Account Manager.

00:07:45.160 --> 00:07:49.590
But the token you get back is
not linked to any API project.

00:07:49.590 --> 00:07:55.150
So, because of that, the Drive
API has no way to know which

00:07:55.150 --> 00:07:57.820
API project is requesting
access to which files.

00:07:57.820 --> 00:08:02.770
And the Drive API introduced
a new set of permissions.

00:08:02.770 --> 00:08:06.350
Like an app can only request
access to files that it has

00:08:06.350 --> 00:08:11.220
access to or the user opened
with these applications.

00:08:11.220 --> 00:08:15.010
And because the Account Manager
doesn't let Google

00:08:15.010 --> 00:08:20.020
Drive know which API project is
requesting access, the API

00:08:20.020 --> 00:08:23.980
won't work when requesting and
an access token with the

00:08:23.980 --> 00:08:25.630
Account Manager.

00:08:25.630 --> 00:08:30.980
So I believe what ASTRO is
currently doing is using the

00:08:30.980 --> 00:08:35.299
old API, which is called the
Documents List API, I

00:08:35.299 --> 00:08:36.679
guess Version 3.

00:08:36.679 --> 00:08:37.159
STEVEN BAZYL: Yeah.

00:08:37.159 --> 00:08:38.360
I believe so as well.

00:08:38.360 --> 00:08:41.429
And it does have some

00:08:41.429 --> 00:08:42.864
disadvantages for mobile devices.

00:08:42.864 --> 00:08:47.530
So some of the features, like
partial retrievals so you can

00:08:47.530 --> 00:08:50.660
be selective in terms of the
fields that you download, is

00:08:50.660 --> 00:08:52.080
not available in that API.

00:08:52.080 --> 00:08:54.460
But it is in the Drive API.

00:08:54.460 --> 00:08:56.440
Actually, it's really important
for mobile apps in

00:08:56.440 --> 00:09:00.240
terms of minimizing bandwidth
usage, so taking advantage of

00:09:00.240 --> 00:09:02.830
things like gzip compression,
selective

00:09:02.830 --> 00:09:04.620
retrieval of fields--

00:09:04.620 --> 00:09:05.960
ALAIN VONGSOUVANH:
JSON metadata.

00:09:05.960 --> 00:09:06.720
STEVEN BAZYL: Yeah, exactly.

00:09:06.720 --> 00:09:11.230
The JSON is just a lot more
compact to begin with.

00:09:11.230 --> 00:09:15.410
I'm really anxious to get them
onto the new API once those

00:09:15.410 --> 00:09:16.890
Play Services are released.

00:09:16.890 --> 00:09:20.010
